verses.text_plain: Now these are the names of the children of Israel, which came into Egypt; every man and his household came with Jacob.
verses.verse_html: 1Now these are the names of the children of Israel, which came into Egypt; every man and his household came with Jacob.

verses.text_plain: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah,
verses.verse_html: 2Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah,

verses.text_plain: Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin,
verses.verse_html: 3Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin,

verses.text_plain: Dan, and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.
verses.verse_html: 4Dan, and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.

verses.text_plain: And all the souls that came out of the loins of Jacob were seventy souls: for Joseph was in Egypt already.
verses.verse_html:
5And all the souls that came out of the loins of Jacob were seventy souls: for Joseph was in Egypt already. ▼
▼ loins: Heb. thigh

verses.text_plain: And Joseph died, and all his brethren, and all that generation.
verses.verse_html: 6And Joseph died, and all his brethren, and all that generation.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel were fruitful, and increased abundantly, and multiplied, and waxed exceeding mighty; and the land was filled with them.
verses.verse_html: 7And the children of Israel were fruitful, and increased abundantly, and multiplied, and waxed exceeding mighty; and the land was filled with them.

verses.text_plain: Now there arose up a new king over Egypt, which knew not Joseph.
verses.verse_html: 8Now there arose up a new king over Egypt, which knew not Joseph.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto his people, Behold, the people of the children of Israel are more and mightier than we:
verses.verse_html: 9And he said unto his people, Behold, the people of the children of Israel are more and mightier than we:

verses.text_plain: Come on, let us deal wisely with them; lest they multiply, and it come to pass, that, when there falleth out any war, they join also unto our enemies, and fight against us, and so get them up out of the land.
verses.verse_html: 10Come on, let us deal wisely with them; lest they multiply, and it come to pass, that, when there falleth out any war, they join also unto our enemies, and fight against us, and so get them up out of the land.

tokens.text: and it come to pass, that, when there falleth out

verses.text_plain: Therefore they did set over them taskmasters to afflict them with their burdens. And they built for Pharaoh treasure cities, Pithom and Raamses.
verses.verse_html: 11Therefore they did set over them taskmasters to afflict them with their burdens. And they built for Pharaoh treasure cities, Pithom and Raamses.

verses.text_plain: But the more they afflicted them, the more they multiplied and grew. And they were grieved because of the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html:
12But the more they afflicted them, the more they multiplied and grew. And they were grieved because of the children of Israel. ▼
▼ But…: Heb. And as they afflicted them, so they multiplied, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ But…: Heb. And as they afflicted them, so they multiplied, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ But…: Heb. And as they afflicted them, so they multiplied, etc

verses.text_plain: And the Egyptians made the children of Israel to serve with rigour:
verses.verse_html: 13And the Egyptians made the children of Israel to serve with rigour:

verses.text_plain: And they made their lives bitter with hard bondage, in morter, and in brick, and in all manner of service in the field: all their service, wherein they made them serve, was with rigour.
verses.verse_html: 14And they made their lives bitter with hard bondage, in morter, and in brick, and in all manner of service in the field: all their service, wherein they made them serve, was with rigour.

tokens.text: and in all manner of service

verses.text_plain: And the king of Egypt spake to the Hebrew midwives, of which the name of the one was Shiphrah, and the name of the other Puah:
verses.verse_html: 15And the king of Egypt spake to the Hebrew midwives, of which the name of the one was Shiphrah, and the name of the other Puah:

verses.text_plain: And he said, When ye do the office of a midwife to the Hebrew women, and see them upon the stools; if it be a son, then ye shall kill him: but if it be a daughter, then she shall live.
verses.verse_html: 16And he said, When ye do the office of a midwife to the Hebrew women, and see them upon the stools; if it be a son, then ye shall kill him: but if it be a daughter, then she shall live.

tokens.text: When ye do the office of a midwife

verses.text_plain: But the midwives feared God, and did not as the king of Egypt commanded them, but saved the men children alive.
verses.verse_html: 17But the midwives feared God, and did not as the king of Egypt commanded them, but saved the men children alive.

verses.text_plain: And the king of Egypt called for the midwives, and said unto them, Why have ye done this thing, and have saved the men children alive?
verses.verse_html: 18And the king of Egypt called for the midwives, and said unto them, Why have ye done this thing, and have saved the men children alive?

verses.text_plain: And the midwives said unto Pharaoh, Because the Hebrew women are not as the Egyptian women; for they are lively, and are delivered ere the midwives come in unto them.
verses.verse_html: 19And the midwives said unto Pharaoh, Because the Hebrew women are not as the Egyptian women; for they are lively, and are delivered ere the midwives come in unto them.

verses.text_plain: Therefore God dealt well with the midwives: and the people multiplied, and waxed very mighty.
verses.verse_html: 20Therefore God dealt well with the midwives: and the people multiplied, and waxed very mighty.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, because the midwives feared God, that he made them houses.
verses.verse_html: 21And it came to pass, because the midwives feared God, that he made them houses.

tokens.text: And it came to pass, because the midwives

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh charged all his people, saying, Every son that is born ye shall cast into the river, and every daughter ye shall save alive.
verses.verse_html: 22And Pharaoh charged all his people, saying, Every son that is born ye shall cast into the river, and every daughter ye shall save alive.
